BT 1 0 0 1 0 182 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL (In this work, we formulate search engines augmented with generative models that we dub) Tj T* (generative engines. We propose Generative Engine Optimization \(GEO\) to empower content) Tj T* (creators to optimize their content under generative engines. We define impression metrics for) Tj T* (generative engines and propose and release GEO-bench: a benchmark encompassing diverse) Tj T* (user queries from multiple domains and settings, along with relevant sources needed to answer) Tj T* (those queries. We propose several ways to optimize content for generative engines and) Tj T* (demonstrate that these methods can boost source visibility by up to $4 0 \\%$ in generative engine) Tj T* (responses. Among other findings, we show that including citations, quotations from relevant) Tj T* (sources, and statistics can significantly boost source visibility. Further, we discover a dependence) Tj T* (of GEO methods\222 effectiveness on the query domain and the potential of combining multiple GEO) Tj T* (strategies in conjunction. We show promising results on a commercially deployed generative) Tj T* (engine with millions of active users, showcasing the real-world impact of our work. In summary, our) Tj T* (work is the first to formalize the important and timely GEO paradigm, releasing algorithms and) Tj T* (infrastructure \(benchmarks, datasets, and metrics\) to facilitate rapid progress in generative engines) Tj T* (by the community. This serves as a first step towards understanding the impact of generative) Tj T* (engines on the digital space and the role of GEO in this new paradigm of search engines.) Tj T* ET
Q
